report_faults:

 [-H]                                  Help text
 [-h]                                  Help text
 [-ALTFAULT <string>]                  Alternate Fault Model
 [-COMET <string>]                     COMET Name(s)
 [-EXPERIMENT <string>]                Experiment Name
 [-LOG no|all|summary|nosummary] (all) Customize Data Written to Log
 [-LOGCOMPRESS yes|no] (no)            Compress the log file
 [-LOGFILE <outfilename>]              Write to specified log file
 [-STDOUT no|all|summary|nosummary] (all) Customize Data Written to STDOUT
 [-TESTMODE <string>]                  Test Mode (Name(s), all, or NONE)
  -WORKDIR <indirectory>               Working Directory
 [-cellawaredefects yes|no] (no)       Report Cell Aware Defects for each pattern fault
 [-cellnamelength <integer>] (20)      Length of Cell Name field (column) in the report
 [-experimentglobal no|yes] (no)       Include experiment status on top of global status
 [-experimentonly no|yes] (no)         Include uncommitted tests experiment status without test mode status
 [-faultlocation net|faultnet|pin|cellpin] (Conditional Default) Use primitive pin names, cell pin names or propagation net names to identify fault location
 [-faults <string>]                    Range of Fault IDs
 [-faultstatus untested|tested|testedthismode|possibly|redundant|aborted|untestable|all[,untested|tested|testedthismode|possibly|redundant|aborted|untestable|all]...] (Conditional Default) Include Only Faults with Specified Fault Status
 [-faulttype static|dynamic|parametric|shortednet|staticbridge|dynamicbridge|iddq|all[,static|dynamic|parametric|shortednet|staticbridge|dynamicbridge|iddq|all]...] (static) Include Only Faults with Specified Types of Faults
 [-help <string>]                      Help Facility
 [-hierend primitive|techcell|macro|<integer>] (Conditional Default) Limit hierarchical list to this many levels deep
 [-hierstart top|<string><integer>]    Report Hierarchical List for Block Name
 [-ignored yes|no] (Conditional Default) Include faults that are identified as ignored
 [-inactive yes|no] (Conditional Default) Include faults that are not active in the selected test mode
 [-inactiveallmodes yes|no] (no)       List Faults that are Not Active in Any Testmode
 [-includecollapsed no|yes] (yes)      Include Collapsed Faults
 [-messagecount <string>]              Limit Messages for Specified Message Id (e.g., messagecount=XXX-710=3).
 [-messagecounteach <integer>]         Default Limit for Each Message.
 [-messagecounteachseverity all|excludeinfo] (all) Level of severity for which messages are to be suppressed as per messagecounteach
 [-powercomponent <string>]            Type(s) of Low Power Components to report
 [-ptab yes|no] (no)                   Include faults that are identified as possibly testable at best
 [-quiet no|yes] (no)                  Quiet
 [-reportdetails no|yes] (no)          Print Long Listing (activation/propagation requirements)
 [-reportkey yes|no] (no)              Print Fault Status Key and Fault Type Key
